S7.title: 12 hour☘️ Study with me LIVE ☕ calm cozy ambience🩺POMODORO🔥Real-time study #Medgirl 2025-05-17 16:48
S7.description:
📩open me:

Hi!
Welcome to another Study with me
Thanks for joining
_________________________

I hope this study video helps you avoid using social media while you study. You will find a quiet and cosy study room ambience in this video when studying at your home. Hopefully, this would get you motivated more for studying. You might hear the rain, birds, typing sounds and the flipping of pages (and cars too, unfortunately) from time to time, and I hope that helps you know that I'm there studying with you!

🔥Key to success - """"BE CONSISTENT""""🔥

___________________________

What are you studying and where are you joining from? I also wonder what type of videos you like, study at the library or study at home? Your opinions are quite important to me; and, if you let me know what type of videos you like to watch, I would be happy. 
_____________________________

✧･ﾟ at the beginning of the study sessions, make sure to:
- turn off anything you're not going to be using to study
- have your materials ready to go
- have drinks/food ready so you don't have to get up to go get necessities
- have a clear idea of what you want to accomplish during the session (i.e., choose a task from your to-do list)


✧･ﾟ during the breaks:
- stop working as soon as the timer hits, even if you're mid-sentence
- make sure to get up, do some simple stretches
- refill anything that needs to get refilled
- talk to friends/update family

✧･ﾟ at the end of this video:
if you want to continue studying, give yourself a longer break and you can the next session video!

you're set to go! ♡
_____________________________
💡Please adjust the volume for each of the background music that comes out.
The ASMR that comes out with 💡 is the sound of burning wood and Rain. 
_____________________________

We have a Chat bot- 🤖
Commands for chat bot- 

!hi - when you join in👋
!start - to start studying
!top - Top Points
!points -  to know your points💯
!complete - when done with the goal

Chat rules:
- Being nice and respectful is mandatory!
- Spamming, harassment, trolling, bullying, repeating and all capital messages are definitely prohibited!
- Please feel encouraged to write in English so no one would feel excluded in the chat :)
- Please check YouTube's Community Guidelines
_____________________________

To those who are starting :
In order to study or do anything for long periods of time you need a strong purpose and you must be willing to endure challenges. If I can do this, think about what you can accomplish. If you're starting out, start from low intervals(10-30 minutes) and gradually increase once you feel you're comfortable. If you feel like quitting, visualize your goals and evaluate your purpose. Learn to accept challenges in your life to become uncommon.

S60.title: “Study with Me” | 50 Min Focus / 10 Min Break Pomodoro 2025-05-17 16:49
S60.description:
Welcome to the ultimate focus zone! 🌱  
This stream runs EVERY DAY, 24 hours, using the **Pomodoro 50 : 10 method**:  
・50 min deep-work session  
・10 min break with soft lo-fi + ambient rain  

⏱️  HOW IT WORKS  
0:00 – 50:00  Focus Block 🖊️  
50:01 – 60:00 Break ☕ (stretch, hydrate, rest your eyes)  
The cycle restarts automatically at the top of every hour.

🎧  AUDIO  
• Lo-fi hip-hop & gentle rain for calm concentration  
• Volume set low so you can keep your own playlist on top if you prefer

📸  WHAT YOU SEE  
• Real-time desk view + on-screen countdown timer  
• Minimalist aesthetic (neutral tones, no distractions)  
• Occasional real-time chat check-ins from me when I’m live 📶

📝  TIPS FOR MAX PRODUCTIVITY  
1. Write down a tiny to-do list for the next 50 minutes.  
2. Put your phone on “Do Not Disturb.”  
3. During the 10-minute break: stand up, stretch, drink water.  
4. Repeat 4 cycles, then take a longer 30-minute break.

💬  CHAT RULES  
• Be kind & respectful—this is a safe study space.  
• No spam, political arguments, or promotion.  
• Feel free to share what you’re working on or your goals!

📅  LIVE SESSIONS  
When I’m actually at my desk I jump on camera & chat.  
When I’m away, you get the pre-recorded study ambience so you can stay in flow.


🌟  SUPPORT THE STREAM  
A simple like 👍 or share 🔗 helps keep this running 24/7!  
Subscribe & click 🔔 so you don’t miss my live check-ins.

S72.description:
⬇️🟢stream schedule, links and faq down below!!🟢⬇️
this channel isn’t just for studying; 

I've been there; I almost killed myself at a railway and stopped studying for half a year, it would be easy to just give up and let life win, but instead I use my situation to drive myself forward even when i dont fucking feel like it.

It can get overwhelming sometimes, especially if like me you have no one to talk to, but if you and me are studying together we've got eachother. Lets get through this together :)

mental health stuff:
due to severe mental health issues I don't talk during my streams in the breaks, its because I go through a lot of shit in my life and I dont want to ruin other people's days by putting negative energy out there. Instead I try to record videos as much as I can where I'm just talking about life stuff, hopefully these videos resonate with some of yall, and I'm sorry I can't talk during the stream I promise it will get better.

studying stuff:
i use the pomodoro technique (120 or 60 mins study / 20 or 10 mins break)
rain sounds during study lofi during break

I am currently working on my PhD dissertation and using livestreams to quietly record my daily writing journey.
No face, no talking—just calmly sitting and writing, little by little.
There are no checklists or set targets; I simply write as much as I can each day.

The main question I want to answer is:

If you are also writing, studying, preparing for exams, or focusing on something important in your life, feel free to join me and challenge yourself.
